Thinking about things to do in Delhi over weekends this Monsoon? Don’t worry we have got you covered!

We’re back with the most amazing plans of this weekend. Monsoon Edition 🤩

DM/Comment/Link in Bio for more information!

Cycling tours are our way to make Delhites explore lanes of Delhi on these special tours and get into details of the history & stories which make Delhi what it is today. We really enjoy doing these tours and connecting more people with Delhi using cycles.

You can book the tour from the link in our bio.

Technical Details:
🕒 Duration: Approx. 3-4 hours (with chai break)

🚲 Inclusions: City cycles, knowledgeable tour leaders, chai in the city lanes, and a treasure trove of Delhi’s stories.

❌ Exclusions: Personal expenses.

🛄What to Bring: Water bottles, caps, raincoat (if needed), comfortable attire and footwear, and most importantly, your curiosity😉! 🚲

More details about the tour can be found in the registration link. Please check our Bio for all the links.

Happy Birthday to our Tour Leader-in-Chief🫡, Himanshu Shekhar (@hr.the.traveler )! 🎂🚴‍♂️

The man who doesn’t just lead tours—he leads a movement. With a heart full of passion for India, its culture, and the planet we call home, Himanshu inspires us every day to reimagine travel as a tool for connection, sustainability, and storytelling.

From the narrow lanes of Old Delhi to global platforms, his vision is clear: a future where travel is slow, meaningful, and mindful. The way he brings people together on two wheels is nothing short of magic.

Drop your best wishes and love in the comments—let’s make his day as amazing as the journeys he creates! 💛🌍✨

latestPosts.caption:
Letters. Cycles. And Chai.
This World Bicycle Day, we did something beautifully old-school — we wrote letters.

Because just like chai, we believe cycling deserves to be a part of everyday Indian life.

With support from our non-profit, Public Mobility Project, and our sustainability partner KLM, we celebrated more than just bicycles. We celebrated a vision — one where cycles are respected as everyday mobility, not just hobbies.

We posted letters to our authorities, asking for a safer, more cycle-friendly India. We talked about health, traffic, pollution — and how pedal power can be a real solution.

🌍 And while doing so, we looked to the Netherlands, a nation that lives and breathes cycling. We’ve learned a lot from them — about infrastructure, culture, and mindset. And there’s still so much more to learn.

Let’s bring our countries — and their ideas — closer, one cycle at a time. Because chai unites us. And so can cycles.

📬 Tell us in the comments — what would you say to your city leaders?
📝 Write your own letter below.
🚴‍♀️ Tag your authorities.
Let’s build a cycling culture as strong as our love for chai.

Video By: @ar.un9992
